verbose_text: In particular, the levels of ZK2B10 (0.55 +/- 0.11 mg/kg, which is translated into 0.09 +/- 0.02 mug/mL) in ZIKV + neonates were well above the IC 50 neutralization values measured in the PRNT, whereas IgG levels in the other mAb groups measured less than or similar to those in the negative control PBS group (XREF_FIG A and XREF_FIG C).
